            <p  class="text-center"><strong>Friday 19 September 2025</strong></p>
            <p  class="text-center">Muniments Room, Cherry Park, Argyll Estates, Inveraray PA32 8XE</p>
            <p>The Scottish Records Association's Annual Conference will be held in the Muniments Room at Cherry Park, the eighteenth-century estates offices at Inveraray Castle, on Friday 19 September. The conference will take a slightly different shape and form this year, with formal conference papers in the morning followed by lunch and a guided tour of Inveraray Jail in the afternoon. The focus of the day is prison records and their use in historical research, reflecting current research using prison records, the type and format of the records themselves, and the development, management and custody of these collections.</p>

            <p>The Scottish Records Association (SRA) was founded in 1977 (Scottish Charity number SC008896) and is concerned with the preservation and use of
historical records in Scotland. It provides a forum for users, owners and custodians of records to discuss matters relating to the records, their custody and conservation and research.</p>

